{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773245124628,"sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","part":{"id":"prt_cdda55012002D5C0A1EZEQnu1q","sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","messageID":"msg_cdda543de001EVRFQ3Ykqshagf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01JAjtkcwXMC98Pqqtw8vEVz","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/agent/wave-worker.md"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/agent/wave-worker.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: ---\n2: description: >-\n3:   Autonomous coding agent launched by wombo into isolated git worktrees to\n4:   implement features from .features.yml. Operates headlessly with no human\n5:   interaction. Launched by `wombo launch` when there are backlog/planned\n6:   features ready for implementation.\n7: \n8:   Examples:\n9: \n10:   - user: \"Implement feature cli-bugs from the backlog\"\n11:     assistant: \"I'll read the feature spec from .features.yml and implement all subtasks.\"\n12: \n13:   - user: \"Fix the build errors from the last run\"\n14:     assistant: \"I'll read the build output, identify the failures, and fix them.\"\n15: mode: primary\n16: ---\n17: You are an autonomous coding agent launched by wombo into an isolated git worktree.\n18: You implement features defined in `.features.yml` with zero human interaction.\n19: \n20: ## Your Environment\n21: \n22: - You are in a **git worktree**, not the main repository. Your branch is `feature/<feature-id>`.\n23: - The feature you must implement was passed to you as a prompt. It includes the full spec: description, subtasks, constraints, forbidden items, references, and build command.\n24: - Config files from the main repo (AGENTS.md, opencode config, this agent definition) have been copied into your worktree.\n25: - **Runtime:** Bun (not Node). TypeScript, strict mode, ESM only.\n26: \n27: ## Operational Rules\n28: \n29: **You run headlessly. You MUST:**\n30: - NEVER ask questions or request clarification. Make reasonable decisions from context and code conventions.\n31: - NEVER enter plan mode or propose plans for approval. Execute directly.\n32: - NEVER wait for confirmation. Act decisively.\n33: - If ambiguity exists, examine the codebase for patterns and follow them.\n34: - If you encounter an error, debug and fix it yourself (up to 3 attempts per issue).\n35: \n36: ## Workflow\n37: \n38: 1. **Read the prompt** — it contains the full feature spec from `.features.yml` including subtasks, constraints, and forbidden items.\n39: 2. **Read AGENTS.md** if present — it contains project-specific hard constraints and conventions.\n40: 3. **Explore the codebase** — understand the architecture before writing code. Read key files, follow imports, understand patterns.\n41: 4. **Plan with TodoWrite** — break the work into concrete steps.\n42: 5. **Implement subtasks in order** — commit after each logical unit of work.\n43: 6. **Typecheck** — run `bun run typecheck` (or the project's equivalent).\n44: 7. **Build** — run the build command from the prompt to verify everything compiles.\n45: 8. **Fix any failures** — if typecheck or build fails, fix and re-run until it passes.\n46: \n47: ## Commit Guidelines\n48: \n49: - Use conventional commits: `feat(scope):`, `fix(scope):`, `refactor(scope):`\n50: - Scope should be the feature ID or a relevant module name\n51: - Commit after each logical unit of work (roughly per subtask)\n52: - Do NOT squash everything into one commit\n53: - Do NOT push to remote — the orchestrator handles that\n54: - Do NOT modify `.features.yml` — the orchestrator handles status updates\n55: \n56: ## Constraints\n57: \n58: - **Stay in scope.** Only implement the feature you were assigned. Do not modify unrelated code.\n59: - **Respect the feature's constraints and forbidden lists.** These are non-negotiable.\n60: - **Build must pass.** The orchestrator will verify your build. If it fails, you'll be retried with the error output.\n61: - **No new dependencies** unless the feature spec explicitly requires them.\n62: - **Follow existing code style** — indentation, naming, patterns, module structure.\n63: \n64: ## Error Recovery\n65: \n66: If something fails:\n67: 1. Read error messages carefully and diagnose the root cause.\n68: 2. Check if the error is in your new code or pre-existing.\n69: 3. Attempt up to 3 fix-and-retry iterations per issue.\n70: 4. If truly blocked by an external factor, document the blocker in a commit message, implement what you can, and move on.\n71: 5. Never leave the worktree in a broken state — if you cannot complete a feature, revert partial changes and document why.\n72: \n73: ## What You Must Never Do\n74: \n75: - Never ask for human input or confirmation\n76: - Never enter plan mode\n77: - Never modify files outside the scope of the current feature\n78: - Never commit code that breaks the build\n79: - Never ignore errors without investigation\n80: - Never push to remote\n\n(End of file - total 80 lines)\n</content>","title":"agent/wave-worker.md","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: >-\n  Autonomous coding agent launched by wombo into isolated git worktrees to\n  implement features from .features.yml. Operates headlessly with no human\n  interaction. Launched by `wombo launch` when there are backlog/planned\n  features ready for implementation.\n\n  Examples:\n\n  - user: \"Implement feature cli-bugs from the backlog\"\n    assistant: \"I'll read the feature spec from .features.yml and implement all subtasks.\"\n\n  - user: \"Fix the build errors from the last run\"\n    assistant: \"I'll read the build output, identify the failures, and fix them.\"\nmode: primary\n---\nYou are an autonomous coding agent launched by wombo into an isolated git worktree.\nYou implement features defined in `.features.yml` with zero human interaction.\n\n## Your Environment","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773245124627,"end":1773245124628}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773245125548,"sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","part":{"id":"prt_cdda5507f001vmBodtM55at2GN","sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","messageID":"msg_cdda543de001EVRFQ3Ykqshagf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01QRJQpA4pZUBzWVDse1d242","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/src/templates/.features.yml"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/src/templates/.features.yml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # =============================================================================\n2: # WOMBO Tracking File - YAML v1.2\n3: # =============================================================================\n4: #\n5: # PURPOSE:\n6: #   Track planned features, their progress, subtasks, and metadata for the\n7: #   project. This file serves as a single source of truth for what's being worked\n8: #   on, what's coming up next, and the history of completed work.\n9: #\n10: # SCHEMA (for LLM and human consumers):\n11: #\n12: #   Each top-level item under `features` is a feature object with these fields:\n13: #\n14: #   id          : string   - Unique kebab-case identifier for the feature.\n15: #   title       : string   - Human-readable short name.\n16: #   description : string   - Detailed explanation of the feature's goal.\n17: #   status      : enum     - One of: backlog, planned, in_progress, blocked,\n18: #                             in_review, done, cancelled.\n19: #   completion  : integer  - Percentage 0–100. Must be 0 when status is\n20: #                             backlog/planned, 100 when done, and reflect\n21: #                             actual progress otherwise.\n22: #   difficulty  : enum     - One of: trivial, easy, medium, hard, very_hard.\n23: #   priority    : enum     - One of: critical, high, medium, low, wishlist.\n24: #   depends_on  : list[string] - IDs of features or subtasks that must be\n25: #                                 completed before this item can start. Use\n26: #                                 an empty list [] when there are no hard\n27: #                                 dependencies. Soft dependencies (recommended\n28: #                                 ordering) should be documented in `notes`\n29: #                                 instead.\n30: #   effort      : string   - Estimated human effort in ISO 8601 duration\n31: #                             (e.g. \"PT2H\" = 2 hours, \"P1D\" = 1 day,\n32: #                             \"P1DT4H\" = 1 day 4 hours).\n33: #   started_at  : string|null - ISO 8601 datetime with timezone when work\n34: #                                began, or null if not yet started.\n35: #   ended_at    : string|null - ISO 8601 datetime with timezone when work\n36: #                                was completed, or null if not yet finished.\n37: #   constraints : list[string] - Technical or process constraints.\n38: #   forbidden   : list[string] - Explicitly forbidden tools, approaches, or\n39: #                                 features (things NOT to do/use).\n40: #   references  : list[string] - URLs or file paths for relevant docs/specs.\n41: #   notes       : list[string] - Free-form status updates, newest first.\n42: #                                 Each entry should be prefixed with an\n43: #                                 ISO 8601 date for chronological tracking.\n44: #   subtasks    : list[subtask] - Ordered breakdown of work. Subtasks use\n45: #                                  the same schema recursively (all fields\n46: #                                  apply, including nested subtasks).\n47: #\n48: # TOP-LEVEL STRUCTURE:\n49: #   features : list[feature]  - Active features in the pipeline (backlog through\n50: #                                in_review). This is where work is planned and\n51: #                                tracked.\n52: #   archive  : list[feature]  - Completed or cancelled features that have\n53: #                                reached the end of their life-cycle (status is\n54: #                                done or cancelled). Move features here once\n55: #                                finished to keep the active list focused.\n56: #                                Same schema as features — full history is\n57: #                                preserved for reference.\n58: #\n59: # STATUS UPDATE CONVENTION:\n60: #   When updating progress, prepend a new entry to the `notes` list with the\n61: #   current ISO 8601 date and a short description of what changed. Example:\n62: #     - \"2026-03-10: Created feature file with initial backlog items.\"\n63: #   This allows chronological tracking while keeping the latest update first.\n64: #\n65: # COMPLETION RULES:\n66: #   - A parent feature's completion should reflect the weighted average of its\n67: #     subtasks, or be set manually if subtask weights are uneven.\n68: #   - When all subtasks are done, the parent must also be marked done (100%).\n69: #   - If any subtask is blocked, consider whether the parent should be blocked.\n70: #\n71: # SUBTASK NESTING:\n72: #   Subtasks can contain their own subtasks to arbitrary depth. The schema is\n73: #   fully recursive. Deeply nested subtasks should be used sparingly - prefer\n74: #   2–3 levels maximum for readability.\n75: #\n76: # =============================================================================\n77: \n78: version: \"1.0\"\n79: \n80: # Metadata about this tracking file\n81: meta:\n82:   created_at: \"2026-03-10T00:00:00+01:00\"\n83:   updated_at: \"2026-03-11T00:00:00+01:00\"\n84:   project: \"fulgidus.github.io\"\n85:   generator: \"Astro 4.x\"\n86:   maintainer: \"fulgidus\"\n87: # =============================================================================\n88: # Active features in the pipeline (backlog through in_review). This is where\n89: # work is planned and tracked.\n90: # =============================================================================\n91: features:\n92: # =============================================================================\n93: # Archive - completed or cancelled features (end of life-cycle)\n94: # =============================================================================\n95: archive:\n96:   \n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/templates/.features.yml","metadata":{"preview":"# =============================================================================\n# WOMBO Tracking File - YAML v1.2\n# =============================================================================\n#\n# PURPOSE:\n#   Track planned features, their progress, subtasks, and metadata for the\n#   project. This file serves as a single source of truth for what's being worked\n#   on, what's coming up next, and the history of completed work.\n#\n# SCHEMA (for LLM and human consumers):\n#\n#   Each top-level item under `features` is a feature object with these fields:\n#\n#   id          : string   - Unique kebab-case identifier for the feature.\n#   title       : string   - Human-readable short name.\n#   description : string   - Detailed explanation of the feature's goal.\n#   status      : enum     - One of: backlog, planned, in_progress, blocked,\n#                             in_review, done, cancelled.\n#   completion  : integer  - Percentage 0–100. Must be 0 when status is\n#                             backlog/planned, 100 when done, and reflect","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773245125541,"end":1773245125547}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773245125665,"sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","part":{"id":"prt_cdda553a6001RqELFoGKhvOEzY","sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","messageID":"msg_cdda543de001EVRFQ3Ykqshagf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01FaScjwqVgSNDGwc5iCicsZ","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/src/lib/launcher.ts"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/src/lib/launcher.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: /**\n2:  * launcher.ts — Process spawning and tmux session management.\n3:  *\n4:  * Responsibilities:\n5:  *   - Launch agent in headless mode (agent run --format json)\n6:  *   - Launch agent in interactive mode (tmux session with TUI)\n7:  *   - Resume sessions for auto-retry\n8:  *   - Manage tmux sessions (create, list, kill)\n9:  */\n10: \n11: import { spawn, execSync, type ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\n12: import { writeFileSync, unlinkSync } from \"node:fs\";\n13: import type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\n14: import { resolveAgentBin } from \"../config.js\";\n15: \n16: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n17: // Types\n18: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n19: \n20: export interface LaunchResult {\n21:   pid: number;\n22:   process: ChildProcess;\n23:   sessionId?: string;\n24: }\n25: \n26: export interface LaunchOptions {\n27:   worktreePath: string;\n28:   featureId: string;\n29:   prompt: string;\n30:   model?: string;\n31:   interactive?: boolean;\n32:   config: WomboConfig;\n33: }\n34: \n35: export interface RetryOptions {\n36:   worktreePath: string;\n37:   featureId: string;\n38:   sessionId: string;\n39:   buildErrors: string;\n40:   model?: string;\n41:   interactive?: boolean;\n42:   config: WomboConfig;\n43: }\n44: \n45: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n46: // Helpers\n47: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n48: \n49: function tmuxSessionName(featureId: string, config: WomboConfig): string {\n50:   return `${config.agent.tmuxPrefix}-${featureId}`;\n51: }\n52: \n53: function runSilent(cmd: string): string {\n54:   try {\n55:     return execSync(cmd, { encoding: \"utf-8\", stdio: \"pipe\" }).trim();\n56:   } catch {\n57:     return \"\";\n58:   }\n59: }\n60: \n61: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n62: // Headless Launch\n63: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n64: \n65: /**\n66:  * Launch agent in headless mode with JSON output.\n67:  */\n68: export function launchHeadless(opts: LaunchOptions): LaunchResult {\n69:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n70: \n71:   const args = [\n72:     \"run\",\n73:     \"--format\", \"json\",\n74:     \"--agent\", opts.config.agent.name,\n75:     \"--dir\", opts.worktreePath,\n76:     \"--title\", `wombo: ${opts.featureId}`,\n77:   ];\n78: \n79:   if (opts.model) {\n80:     args.push(\"--model\", opts.model);\n81:   }\n82: \n83:   args.push(opts.prompt);\n84: \n85:   const child = spawn(agentBin, args, {\n86:     stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"],\n87:     detached: false,\n88:     env: {\n89:       ...process.env,\n90:       OPENCODE_DIR: opts.worktreePath,\n91:     },\n92:   });\n93: \n94:   // Close stdin so agent starts processing immediately\n95:   child.stdin?.end();\n96: \n97:   return {\n98:     pid: child.pid!,\n99:     process: child,\n100:   };\n101: }\n102: \n103: /**\n104:  * Resume a headless session with a retry message (build errors).\n105:  */\n106: export function retryHeadless(opts: RetryOptions): LaunchResult {\n107:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n108: \n109:   const retryMessage = `The build failed. Please fix the following errors and run \\`${opts.config.build.command}\\` again:\\n\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n${opts.buildErrors}\\n\\`\\`\\`\\n\\nFix all errors, then verify the build passes.`;\n110: \n111:   const args = [\n112:     \"run\",\n113:     \"--format\", \"json\",\n114:     \"--session\", opts.sessionId,\n115:     \"--continue\",\n116:     \"--dir\", opts.worktreePath,\n117:   ];\n118: \n119:   if (opts.model) {\n120:     args.push(\"--model\", opts.model);\n121:   }\n122: \n123:   args.push(retryMessage);\n124: \n125:   const child = spawn(agentBin, args, {\n126:     stdio: [\"pipe\", \"pipe\", \"pipe\"],\n127:     detached: false,\n128:     env: {\n129:       ...process.env,\n130:       OPENCODE_DIR: opts.worktreePath,\n131:     },\n132:   });\n133: \n134:   child.stdin?.end();\n135: \n136:   return {\n137:     pid: child.pid!,\n138:     process: child,\n139:   };\n140: }\n141: \n142: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n143: // Interactive (tmux) Launch\n144: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n145: \n146: /**\n147:  * Launch agent in a tmux session for interactive use.\n148:  */\n149: export function launchInteractive(opts: LaunchOptions): LaunchResult {\n150:   const agentBin = resolveAgentBin(opts.config);\n151:   const sessionName = tmuxSessionName(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n152: \n153:   // Kill existing session if any\n154:   killTmuxSession(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n155: \n156:   // Build the agent command to run inside tmux\n157:   const ocArgs = [\n158:     agentBin,\n159:     \"--dir\", JSON.stringify(opts.worktreePath),\n160:   ];\n161: \n162:   if (opts.model) {\n163:     ocArgs.push(\"--model\", JSON.stringify(opts.model));\n164:   }\n165: \n166:   const tmuxCmd = ocArgs.join(\" \");\n167: \n168:   // Create a detached tmux session running the agent\n169:   execSync(\n170:     `tmux new-session -d -s \"${sessionName}\" -c \"${opts.worktreePath}\" \"${tmuxCmd}\"`,\n171:     { stdio: \"pipe\" }\n172:   );\n173: \n174:   // Send the prompt as initial message after a brief delay\n175:   setTimeout(() => {\n176:     try {\n177:       const tmpFile = `/tmp/wombo-prompt-${opts.featureId}.txt`;\n178:       writeFileSync(tmpFile, opts.prompt);\n179:       execSync(`tmux load-buffer \"${tmpFile}\"`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n180:       execSync(`tmux paste-buffer -t \"${sessionName}\"`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n181:       execSync(`tmux send-keys -t \"${sessionName}\" Enter`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n182:       try { unlinkSync(tmpFile); } catch {}\n183:     } catch {\n184:       // If prompt sending fails, user can type manually\n185:     }\n186:   }, 3000);\n187: \n188:   // Get the PID of the tmux server pane process\n189:   const panePid = runSilent(\n190:     `tmux list-panes -t \"${sessionName}\" -F \"#{pane_pid}\"`\n191:   );\n192: \n193:   return {\n194:     pid: parseInt(panePid) || 0,\n195:     process: null as any, // No direct process handle in tmux mode\n196:   };\n197: }\n198: \n199: /**\n200:  * Resume an interactive session with retry message.\n201:  */\n202: export function retryInteractive(opts: RetryOptions): LaunchResult {\n203:   const sessionName = tmuxSessionName(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n204: \n205:   const exists = tmuxSessionExists(opts.featureId, opts.config);\n206: \n207:   if (exists) {\n208:     const retryMsg = `The build failed. Fix these errors:\\n${opts.buildErrors}`;\n209:     const tmpFile = `/tmp/wombo-retry-${opts.featureId}.txt`;\n210:     writeFileSync(tmpFile, retryMsg);\n211:     execSync(`tmux load-buffer \"${tmpFile}\"`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n212:     execSync(`tmux paste-buffer -t \"${sessionName}\"`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n213:     execSync(`tmux send-keys -t \"${sessionName}\" Enter`, { stdio: \"pipe\" });\n214:     try { unlinkSync(tmpFile); } catch {}\n215: \n216:     const panePid = runSilent(\n217:       `tmux list-panes -t \"${sessionName}\" -F \"#{pane_pid}\"`\n218:     );\n219: \n220:     return {\n221:       pid: parseInt(panePid) || 0,\n222:       process: null as any,\n223:     };\n224:   }\n225: \n226:   // Session doesn't exist — launch a new interactive session\n227:   return launchInteractive({\n228:     worktreePath: opts.worktreePath,\n229:     featureId: opts.featureId,\n230:     prompt: `Continue from session ${opts.sessionId}. The build failed:\\n${opts.buildErrors}\\n\\nFix all errors and verify the build passes.`,\n231:     model: opts.model,\n232:     interactive: true,\n233:     config: opts.config,\n234:   });\n235: }\n236: \n237: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n238: // tmux Session Management\n239: // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n240: \n241: /**\n242:  * Check if a tmux session exists for a feature.\n243:  */\n244: export function tmuxSessionExists(\n245:   featureId: string,\n246:   config: WomboConfig\n247: ): boolean {\n248:   const sessionName = tmuxSessionName(featureId, config);\n249:   return runSilent(`tmux has-session -t \"${sessionName}\" 2>/dev/null && echo yes`) === \"yes\";\n250: }\n251: \n252: /**\n253:  * Kill a tmux session for a feature.\n254:  */\n255: export function killTmuxSession(\n256:   featureId: string,\n257:   config: WomboConfig\n258: ): void {\n259:   const sessionName = tmuxSessionName(featureId, config);\n260:   runSilent(`tmux kill-session -t \"${sessionName}\" 2>/dev/null`);\n261: }\n262: \n263: /**\n264:  * List all wombo-related tmux sessions.\n265:  */\n266: export function listTmuxSessions(config: WomboConfig): string[] {\n267:   const output = runSilent(\n268:     `tmux list-sessions -F \"#{session_name}\" 2>/dev/null`\n269:   );\n270:   if (!output) return [];\n271:   return output\n272:     .split(\"\\n\")\n273:     .filter((s) => s.startsWith(config.agent.tmuxPrefix + \"-\"));\n274: }\n275: \n276: /**\n277:  * Kill all wombo-related tmux sessions.\n278:  */\n279: export function killAllTmuxSessions(config: WomboConfig): number {\n280:   const sessions = listTmuxSessions(config);\n281:   for (const s of sessions) {\n282:     runSilent(`tmux kill-session -t \"${s}\" 2>/dev/null`);\n283:   }\n284:   return sessions.length;\n285: }\n286: \n287: /**\n288:  * Check if a process is still running by PID.\n289:  */\n290: export function isProcessRunning(pid: number): boolean {\n291:   if (!pid || pid <= 0) return false;\n292:   try {\n293:     process.kill(pid, 0);\n294:     return true;\n295:   } catch {\n296:     return false;\n297:   }\n298: }\n\n(End of file - total 298 lines)\n</content>","title":"src/lib/launcher.ts","metadata":{"preview":"/**\n * launcher.ts — Process spawning and tmux session management.\n *\n * Responsibilities:\n *   - Launch agent in headless mode (agent run --format json)\n *   - Launch agent in interactive mode (tmux session with TUI)\n *   - Resume sessions for auto-retry\n *   - Manage tmux sessions (create, list, kill)\n */\n\nimport { spawn, execSync, type ChildProcess } from \"node:child_process\";\nimport { writeFileSync, unlinkSync } from \"node:fs\";\nimport type { WomboConfig } from \"../config.js\";\nimport { resolveAgentBin } from \"../config.js\";\n\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n// Types\n// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nexport interface LaunchResult {","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773245125658,"end":1773245125665}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1773245126163,"sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","part":{"id":"prt_cdda5541b001mFIzn5ESsAiiVn","sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","messageID":"msg_cdda543de001EVRFQ3Ykqshagf","type":"tool","callID":"toolu_01CCKRESMGz62x1jMJZYWphw","tool":"read","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/wombo.json"},"output":"<path>/home/fulgidus/Documents/wombo-agent-template-lifecycle/wombo.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: {\n2:   \"featuresFile\": \".features.yml\",\n3:   \"baseBranch\": \"main\",\n4:   \"build\": {\n5:     \"command\": \"bun run build\",\n6:     \"timeout\": 300000,\n7:     \"artifactDir\": \"dist\"\n8:   },\n9:   \"install\": {\n10:     \"command\": \"bun install\",\n11:     \"timeout\": 120000\n12:   },\n13:   \"git\": {\n14:     \"branchPrefix\": \"feature/\",\n15:     \"worktreePrefix\": \"wombo-\",\n16:     \"remote\": \"origin\",\n17:     \"mergeStrategy\": \"--no-ff\"\n18:   },\n19:   \"agent\": {\n20:     \"bin\": null,\n21:     \"name\": \"wave-worker\",\n22:     \"configFiles\": [\n23:       \".opencode/\",\n24:       \"opencode.json\",\n25:       \"AGENTS.md\",\n26:       \"agent/\"\n27:     ],\n28:     \"tmuxPrefix\": \"wombo\"\n29:   },\n30:   \"defaults\": {\n31:     \"maxConcurrent\": 10,\n32:     \"maxRetries\": 5\n33:   }\n34: }\n\n(End of file - total 34 lines)\n</content>","title":"wombo.json","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"featuresFile\": \".features.yml\",\n  \"baseBranch\": \"main\",\n  \"build\": {\n    \"command\": \"bun run build\",\n    \"timeout\": 300000,\n    \"artifactDir\": \"dist\"\n  },\n  \"install\": {\n    \"command\": \"bun install\",\n    \"timeout\": 120000\n  },\n  \"git\": {\n    \"branchPrefix\": \"feature/\",\n    \"worktreePrefix\": \"wombo-\",\n    \"remote\": \"origin\",\n    \"mergeStrategy\": \"--no-ff\"\n  },\n  \"agent\": {\n    \"bin\": null,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"time":{"start":1773245126160,"end":1773245126163}}}}
