{"type":"text","timestamp":1773245398338,"sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","part":{"id":"prt_cdda95d49001qGgodbuHYpVAQ3","sessionID":"ses_3225b064fffe2278ZpH9B8kavM","messageID":"msg_cdda94fe20013AcdK3U9YnRUCz","type":"text","text":"All subtasks are complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Subtask 1: Ship wave-worker.md as bundled template (`51b2543`)\n- Created `src/templates/wave-worker.md` — the canonical agent definition template, identical to the existing `agent/wave-worker.md`\n- Created `src/lib/templates.ts` — template path resolver using `import.meta.dir` (matching the pattern from `features.ts`)\n- Updated `package.json` `files` array to include the new template for distribution\n\n### Subtask 2: Install agent template during init (`0b8d958`)\n- Modified `src/commands/init.ts` to create the `agent/` directory and write the wave-worker.md template into it during `wombo init`\n- Added `yesNo` method to the `Prompter` class for overwrite confirmation\n- If `agent/<name>.md` already exists and `--force` is not set, prompts the user before overwriting\n- Ensures `agent/` is in the `configFiles` array in the generated `wombo.json`\n\n### Subtask 3: Guard agent definition on launch (`2df10d0`)\n- Added `ensureAgentDefinition()` function to `src/lib/templates.ts`\n- At the start of `cmdLaunch`, checks if the agent definition file exists at `agent/<agentName>.md`\n- If missing, reinstalls from the bundled template with a yellow warning message\n- Gracefully handles installation failures without blocking the launch\n\n### Subtask 4: Verify config files copied into worktrees (`72f903a`)\n- Added `verifyConfigFiles()` function to `src/lib/worktree.ts`\n- Called after the config file copy loop in `createWorktree()`\n- Checks each `configFiles` entry that exists in the source project to confirm it was copied into the worktree\n- Logs a warning with the list of missing files if any are absent","time":{"start":1773245398338,"end":1773245398338}}}
